<p>We just wanted to email you a quick note following on from the Gathering. It was a great time and thanks for making it go so well.</p>
<p>There are just three things to follow up.</p>
<p>1. As members we should all be beginning to apply the practices. They are all on the practice cards we handed out. (Let us know if you want another copy and we&rsquo;ll post one to you). We realise it will take some time for them to become regular &lsquo;rhythms&rsquo; of our life but we should all now be reading a gospel (<a href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=mark;&version=51;">Mark</a> for this month) and praying weekly for our team mates as well as our ongoing regular involvement with young people. </p>
<p>It would be good to plan to have another two or three happening by the end of May such as meeting weekly with a prayer partner and thinking about who to meet with as a spiritual coach/mentor each term. Look outside of YFC folk for this. An elder, pastor, home group leader etc would be ideal.</p>
<p>When you have your next team meeting also begin to think how you can assist with a non YFC project this year. Two examples already happening are; From Hamilton helping with the clean up after a Council family event that coincides with Halloween and from Gisborne spending a half day cleaning up a beach (ask your council for potential locations). Make this a fun time where we get to show the wider community the servant aspect of being a Jesus follower.</p>
<p>Discipleship teas have been happening in some areas for a long time but for those where this is new why not try the idea of booking a caf&eacute; and sit round a table or tables asking yourselves some questions such as &ldquo;How have we clearly shown Jesus in our Rock Solid, atomic etc and have someone share for 10 minutes on the subject. If there are only a few of you that is ok. Numbers are not the key, attendance by members is. Make sure the evening is enjoyable. Potential YFC folk who attend should want to come because they pick up you want to be there. You could do the same from a home. These will build as we develop and grow.</p>
<p>2. North Island Training and South Island Training have been renamed 'Converge'. Converge for the North Island is on from the 29th April &ndash; 1 May. Go to the YFC website <a href="http://www.yfc.org.nz/private/registration">http://www.yfc.org.nz/private/registration</a> to find out details and to register. We realise it is following on very closely from the Gathering but for this year it has been unavoidable. Be assured it will not be a repeat but will follow on from the Gathering. Feel free to bring others that are interested in being a part of YFC. The emphasis is on spiritual formation rather than training. We are expecting all North island Members to attend. </p>
<p>South Island 'Converge' will be later in the year and John Brooks (<a href="mailto:j.brooks@yfc.org.nz">j.brooks@yfc.org.nz</a>) will let you know details.</p>
<p>3. <a href="http://www.ctc.net.nz">CTC</a>. Many of you have had or are having Expressions. Remember to let Tracy (<a href="mailto:t.bedford@yfc.org.nz">t.bedford@yfc.org.nz</a>) or Dave (<a href="mailto:d.treeby@yfc.org.nz">d.treeby@yfc.org.nz</a>) know if you need help.   After CTC on the Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday till lunch time we have YFCC (Youth for Christ Conference). Tony Campolo will be speaking to us on the Monday night and Tuesday morning and then we are having a time of refreshment for all members that attend. This will include such things as people coming in to pray for people, a session on looking after yourself and hopefully some Doctors, physiotherapists etc. The focus is on getting renewed and refreshed for the second half of the year. More on this later.</p>
<p>So be assured that you are a part of a bigger work that God is doing around the world. Take a minute and read <a href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=1%20corinthians%2015:58&version1=51">1 Corinthians 15:58</a> (from the living Bible if possible).</p>
